{
  "texts": [
    "-Then, trained a Logistic Regression classifier to predict top college majors using the embedding as input features.",
    "-Vector projection-based bias attenuation method to gender-debias the recommendations.",
    "-Train-test split: 70/30% -Normalized discounted cumulative gain at K Higher NDCG@K means better accuracy -Non-parity unfairness.",
    "Lower UPAR means fairer system.",
    "-T-test for user acceptance study GenderDebiased: NDCCG@3: 0.005 NDCCG@10: 0.01 NDCCG@20: 0.013 U PAR = 1.1188 Mean t-test acceptance score: 0.279 GenderAware: NDCCG@3: 0.0009 NDCCG@10: 0.005 NDCCG@20: 0.007 U PAR = 1.1445 Mean t-test acceptance score: 0.372 -ML evaluation showed that the gender-debiased recommender is fairer and more accurate than gender-aware recommender but online user study showed that participants prefer the biased system."
  ]
}